featured_reviews.review_translated_text:
The word "mosque" denotes a Muslim house of worship where every person can go and pray to Allah. The word evolved from the Arabic term masjid, which means "place of prostration." During prayer, Muslims briefly kneel and touch their foreheads to the ground as a sign of submission to the will of Allah.
The word "mosque" refers to a Muslim place of worship where every person can go and pray to Allah. The term is derived from the Arabic word masjid, meaning "place of prostration". During prayer, Muslims briefly kneel and rest their foreheads on the ground, surrendering to God's will.

featured_reviews.review_id: This mosque is very beautiful. There is good management here. There was too crowd in juma but I felt no any problem. First time I visited in this mosque. When I visited in this mosque ,I felt that there is no space but when I entered, a person gentured me to go upstairs. When I went upstairs, I saw that there was no space there either. I saw that there is also a man standing there who is gesturing to go higher. By doing this we reched the top floor and offered namaz there. There was an empty space. I have seen such management for the first time which I liked very much. This mosque is located in main Patna juction. So I think there would always be a crowd here.
